!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

heavy /ˈhɛvɪ/

(heavier,heavies,heaviest) 

1. ADJ Something that is heavy weighs a lot. 重的 

例： These scissors are awfully heavy. 这些剪刀非常重。 

2. heaviness N-UNCOUNT 沉重 

例： ...a sensation of warmth and heaviness in the muscles. …一种肌肉的温暖和沉重感。 

3. ADJ You use heavy to ask or talk about how much someone or something weighs. 重的 

例： How heavy are you? 你有多重？ 

4. ADJ Heavy means great in amount, degree, or intensity. 大量的; 过度的; 强烈的 

例： Heavy fighting has been going on. 激战一直在进行。 

例： He worried about her heavy drinking. 他为她的酗酒感到担忧。 

5. heavily ADV 大量地; 过度地; 强烈地 

例： It has been raining heavily all day. 一整天雨都下得很大。 

6. ADJ A heavy meal is large in amount and often difficult to digest. 量大而难以消化的 

例： He had been feeling drowsy, the effect of an unusually heavy meal. 他一直感到昏昏欲睡，因为吃了一顿异常量大而难以消化的饭、菜。 

7. ADJ Something that is heavy with things is full of them or loaded with them. 充满了…的 [文学性] [v-link ADJ 'with' n] 

例： The air is heavy with moisture. 空气中充满了湿气。 

8. ADJ If a person's breathing is heavy , it is very loud and deep. 粗重的 (呼吸) 

例： Her breathing became slow and heavy. 她的呼吸变得缓慢而粗重。 

9. heavily ADV 粗重地 [ADV after v] 

例： She sank back on the pillow and closed her eyes, breathing heavily as if asleep. 她躺回到枕头上，闭上双眼，呼吸粗重，就像睡熟了似的。 

10. ADJ A heavy movement or action is done with a lot of force or pressure. 粗重的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...a heavy blow on the back of the skull. …后脑勺上的一记重击。 

11. heavily ADV 粗重地 [ADV after v] 

例： I sat down heavily on the ground beside the road. 我重重地坐在路边的地上。 

12. ADJ A heavy machine or piece of military equipment is very large and very powerful. 重型的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...government militia backed by tanks and heavy artillery. …有坦克和重炮支持的政府民兵组织。 

13. ADJ If you describe a period of time or a schedule as heavy , you mean it involves a lot of work. 繁忙的 

例： It's been a heavy day and I'm tired. 这是繁忙的一天，我累坏了。 

14. ADJ Heavy work requires a lot of strength or energy. 繁重的 

例： The business is thriving and Philippa employs two full-timers for the heavy work. 生意很兴隆，于是菲莉帕雇了两名全职员工来干重活儿。 

15. ADJ If you say that something is heavy on another thing, you mean that it uses a lot of that thing or too much of that thing. 耗费…的 [v-link ADJ 'on' n] 

例： Tanks are heavy on fuel, destructive to roads and difficult to park. 坦克耗油量大，对道路有破坏性，并且难以停放。 

16. ADJ Air or weather that is heavy is unpleasantly still, hot, and damp. (空气或天气) 阴沉的; 闷热的; 潮湿的 

例： The outside air was heavy and moist and sultry. 户外的空气阴沉、潮湿而闷热。 

17. ADJ A situation that is heavy is serious and difficult to cope with. 棘手的 [非正式] 

例： I don't want any more of that heavy stuff. 我可再也不想碰那种麻烦事儿了。 

18. N-COUNT A heavy is a large strong man who is employed to protect a person or place, often by using violence. You can also use heavy to refer to a male character who represents such a man in a film or play. 保镖; 打手 [非正式] 

例： They had employed heavies to evict squatters from neighbouring sites. 他们雇了一些打手，以赶走来自邻近地区的私自占地者。 

例： In 1943, he received his first role as a heavy in 'Double Indemnity.' 1943年，他接了第一个角色，在影片《双重保险》中扮演保镖。

